name: '57 Chevy with a White License Plate
recipe: 1. Fill a glass with ice. Then add 1 shot of both white creme de cacao and vodka. Stir and Serve

name: 155 Belmont
recipe: Use 1 shot of Dark Rum 2 shots of Light Rum 1 shot of Vodka and 1 shot of Orange Juice. Blend with ice. Serve in a wine glass. Garnish with carrot.

name: 9 1/2 Weeks
recipe: Combine 2 shots of Absolute Citron, 1/2 shot of Orange Liqueur, 1 shot of Strawberry Liqueur and 1 shot of Orange Juice ingredients in glass mixer. Chill and strain into Cocktail glass. Garnish with sliced strawberry.

name: A Gilligan's Island
recipe: Combine 1 shot of vodka, 1 shot of Peach Schnapps, 1 shot of Orange juice, 1 shot of Cranberry Juice in a cocktail shaker. Once shaken, pour into glass.

name: A True Amaretto Sour
recipe: Rub the rim of an old fashioned glass with lemon, and dip repeatedly into granulated sugar until it has a good frosted rim. Shake a jigger of Amaretto with the juice of 1/2 a lemon. Strain into glass and add ice. Garnish with a Maraschino Cherry.

name: A.D.M. (After Dinner Mint)
recipe: In a shaker add 1/2 a shot of Creme de Menthe, 3/4 of a shot of Southern Comfort, 1/2 a shot of vodka. Shake pour into a tall glass and top up with Hot Chocolate

name: A1
recipe: Pour all ingredients 2 shots of Gin, 1 shot of Grand Marnier, 1/4 shot of Lemon Juice, dash of Grenadine into a cocktail shaker, mix and serve over ice into a chilled glass.

name: Abbey Martini
recipe: Put 2 shots of Gin, 1 shot of Sweet Vermouth, 1 shot of Orange Juice and a dash of Angustura Bitters into a shaker and mix, then strain contents into a chilled cocktail glass.

name: Absolut Summertime
recipe: Add all ingredients except lemon to shaker. 2 shots of Absolute Citron, 1/2 shot of Sweet and Sour, 1 shot of Sprite, 3 shots of Soda Water. Fill with ice. Cover and shake vigorously. Strain contents into ice filled collins glass. Garnish with lemon.

name: Absolutely Fabulous
recipe: Mix 1 shot of Vodka and 2 shots of Cranberry juice together in a shaker and strain into a glass. Top up with Champagne.

name: Absolutly Screwed Up
recipe: Shake up 1shot of Absolute Citron, Orange Juice and TripleSec, it tastes better that way, but you can stir it if you want. Top up with Ginger Ale.

name: Ace
recipe: Shake all the ingredients in a cocktail shaker. 2 shots of Gin, 1/2 shot of Grenadine, 1/2 shot of Harveys Cream Sherry, 1/2 a shot of Milk and 1/2 a shot of Egg White and ice then strain in a cold glass.

name: Adam & Eve
recipe: Shake together 1 shot of Gin, 1 shot of Cognac, 1 shot of Creme de Cacao and a dash of lemon juice. Strain into a cold glass.

name: Addington
recipe: Mix 2 shots of Sweet Vermouth and 1 shot of Dry Vermouth in a shaker and strain into a cold glass. Top up with a squirt of Soda Water.

name: Addison
recipe: Shake together all the ingredients 2 shots of Gin 1 shot of Vermouth and strain into a cold glass.

name: Addison Special
recipe: Combine 1 shot of Vodka and 1/2 a shot of Grenadine into a shaker. Fill half full with ice and top up with orange juice and shake well. Strain into glass with ice and garnish with a cherry and orange wedge.

name: Adios Amigos Cocktail
recipe: Shake together 1 shot of Rum 1/2 shot of Dry Vermouth 1/2 shot of Cognac 1/2 shot of Gin and strain into a cold glass. Add fresh lime and sugar syrup.

name: Afterglow
recipe: Mix 1hot of Grenadine and 4 shots of Orange Juice and 4 shots of Pineapple Juice. Serve over ice.

name: Alice Cocktail
recipe: Mix 1 shot of Grenadine, 1 shot of Orange Juice, 2 shots of Pineapple Juice and 4 shots of cream. Strain into a large cocktail glass.

name: Apple Karate
recipe: Place 2 cups of Apple Juice and 1 large carrot in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.

name: Applejack
recipe: Add 1 shot of Jack Daniels 1/2 a shot of Midori and 2 shots of Sours into mixing glass, chill and strain into cocktail glass

name: Arizona Stingers
recipe: Place ice cubes in the hurricane glass . Add the 2 shots of Absolute Vodka (Note: You can add as many shots of Absolute as you want!) Fill the rest of glass with the Iced tea with lemon. Stir to mix using a spoon. Drink up and enjoy!!!!!!!

name: Arizona Twister
recipe: Just mix in the 1 shot of rum, vodka, and tequila. Add splashes of the three juices, orange, pineapple and coconut. Heavy on the pineapple. Top off with grenadine. Crushed ice should already be in glass. Top off the glass with a pineapple wedge.

name: Army special
recipe: Pour 1 shot of Vodka, 1 shot of Gin and 1 shot of lime cordial into glass, and top up with crushed ice. Wait for ice to melt slightly and sip without a straw.

name: Aviation
recipe: Add 4 shots of gin 1 shot of lemon juice and 1 shot of cherry liqueur into cocktail shaker filled with ice. Shake well and strain into cocktail glass. Garnish with a cherry.

name: Bora Bora
recipe: Put 10 shots of Pineapple Juice 6 shots of Passion Fruit and 1 shot of lemon juice and 1 shot of Grenadine in a blender or shaker, serve in a highball glass on the rocks. Garnish with 1 slice of pineapple and one cherry.

name: Cherry Electric Lemonade
recipe: Place 1 shot of each of the following Gin, Tequila, Vodka, White Rum, Triple Sec, Cherry Liqueur and Sours. Now stir vigorously and then pour over a large cup of ice and top up with Soda Water. Now drink it with a straw and stir occasionally.

name: Cosmopolitan
recipe: Add 1 shot of each of the following Absolute Citron Lime Juice Cointreau Cranberry Juice into cocktail shaker filled with ice. Shake well and double strain into large cocktail glass. Garnish with lime wheel.

name: Cosmopolitan Martini
recipe: Pour 1 shot of each of the following, Cointreau, Vodka, Lime, Cranberry Juice, into a mixing glass half filled with ice, shake and strain into chilled Martini glass.

name: Cream Soda
recipe: Pour 1oz of Spiced Rum into a highball glass with ice. Fill with Ginger Ale.

name: Dark Caipirinha
recipe: Muddle the sugar into the lime wedges in an old-fashioned glass. Fill the glass with ice cubes. Pour the cachaca into the glass. Stir well.

name: Dirty Martini
recipe: Pour the 5 shots of vodka, 1 shot of dry vermouth and 2 shots of olive brine into a cocktail shaker with a handful of ice and shake well. Rub the rim of a martini glass with the wedge of lemon. Strain the contents of the cocktail shaker into the glass and add the olive. A dirty Martini contains a splash of olive brine or olive juice and is typically garnished with an olive.

name: Espresso Martini
recipe: Pour 1 shot of vodka, 1 shot of Kahlua and a dash of sugar syrup into shaker filled with ice, shake vigorously, and strain into chilled martini glass

name: Flaming Lamborghini
recipe: Pour one shot of Sambuca and one shot of Kahlua into the Cocktail Glass and give the drinker a straw. Pour 1 shot of Baileys and 1 shot of Blue Curacao into two separate shot glasses either side of the cocktail glass. Set alight the concoction in the cocktail glass and start to drink through the straw (this drink should be drunk in one) , as the bottom of the glass is reached put out the fire by pouring the Baileys and  Blue Curacao into the cocktail glass and keep drinking till it's all gone!!

name: French Martini
recipe: Pour 3 shots of vodka 1 shot of Raspberry liqueur adn 1 shot of pineapple juice into shaker with ice cubes. Shake well and strain into a chilled cocktail glass. Squeeze oil from lemon peel onto the drink.

name: Gagliardo
recipe: Mix 3 shots of Peach Vodka, 1 shot of Lemon juice, 1 shot of Galliano and a dash of sugar syrup. Shake well and serve in a cocktail glass. This is a home cocktail of American/Internet Bar del Pozzo, Pavia, Italy.

name: Gin Rickey
recipe: Half-fill a tall glass with ice. Mix 2 shots of gin and 1 shot of Grenadine together and pour over the ice. Add the lime or lemon juice and top off with soda water. Decorate the glass with lime and/or lemon slices.

name: Imperial Cocktail
recipe: Shake with ice 4 shots of Lime Juice 2 shots of Gin and 2 shots of Aperol and strain into cocktail glass.

name: Irish Curdling Cow
recipe: Pour 1 shot of each of the following Irish Cream, Vodka, and Bourbon in a glass. Add some ice and mix in 3 shots of orange juice.

name: Lemon Drop
recipe: Shake and strain 1 shot of Vodka and 1 shot of Cointreau into a chilled cocktail glass rimmed with sugar.

name: Malibu Twister
recipe: Add 2 shots of rum & 2 shots of tropicana then, add 1 shot of cranberry juice, stir

name: Martinez Cocktail
recipe: Stir 1 shot of Gin 1 shot of Dry Vermouth 1/2 shot of Triple Sec and a dash of orange bitters (except cherry) with ice and strain into a cocktail glass. Top with the cherry and serve.

name: Martini
recipe: Straight: Pour 2 shots of Gin and 1/2 shot of Vermouth into a mixing glass with ice cubes. Stir well. Strain in chilled martini cocktail glass. Squeeze oil from lemon peel onto the drink, or garnish with olive.

name: Mary Pickford
recipe: Shake 2 shots of Light Rum 1 shot of Pineapple Juice 1/2 shot of cherry liqueur and 1/2 shot of Grendine. Strain into a chilled large cocktail glass

name: Midnight Mint
recipe: If available, rim cocktail (Martini) glass with sugar syrup then dip into chocolate flakes or powder. Add 1 shot of Baileys and 3/4 shot of Creme de Menthe and 3/4 of Cream into shaker with ice. Shake well then strain into cocktail glass.

name: Mojito
recipe: Muddle mint leaves with sugar and the juice of 1 lime. Add a splash of soda water and fill the glass with cracked ice. Pour in 1 shot of light rum and top with soda water. Garnish and serve with straw.

name: New York Lemonade
recipe: Serve in a chilled cocktail glass. Lemon and sugar the rim. Stir the following ingredients together 2 shots of Absolute Citron 1 shot of Grand Marnier 2 shots of Lemon Juice and a squirt of soda. Then Strain.

name: Old Fashioned
recipe: Place sugar cube in old fashioned glass and saturate with bitters, add a dash of plain water. Muddle until dissolved. Fill the glass with ice cubes and add Bourbon. Garnish with orange twist, and a cocktail cherry.

name: Orangeade
recipe: Place some ice cubes in a large tumbler or highball glass, add 1 shot of lemon juice, 3 shots of orange juice, sugar syrup, and stir well. Top up with cold soda water, serve with a drinking straw.

name: Pisco Sour
recipe: Vigorously shake and strain 2 shots of Pisco and 1 shot of Lemon Juice in a cocktail shaker with ice cubes, then pour into glass and garnish with bitters.[1]

name: Rail Splitter
recipe: Mix sugar syrup with lemon juice in a tall glass. Fill up with ginger ale.

name: Ruby Tuesday
recipe: Pour 2 shots of gin and 5 shots of cranberry juice into a highball filled with ice cubes. Add a splash of grenadine and stir.

name: Shark Attack
recipe: Mix 1 can of lemonade with 3 cans of water. Mix into pitcher. Add 1 1/2 cup of Vodka (Absolut). Mix well. Pour into glass of crushed ice. Excellent!

name: Tequila Sunrise
recipe: Pour 2 shots of tequila and 4 shots of orange juice into glass over ice. Add a dash of grenadine, which will sink to the bottom. Stir gently to create the sunrise effect. Garnish and serve.

name: The Evil Blue Thing
recipe: Pour 1.5 shots of Creme de Cacao, 1 shot of Blue Curacao and 1/2 shot of  Light Rum into a glass, and drop in a blue whale! The blue whale isn't really necessary, but it makes the drink more fun.

name: Vesper
recipe: Shake 4 shots of Gin, 1 shot of Vodka and 1/2 shot of Lillet Blanc over ice until well chilled, then strain into a deep goblet and garnish with a thin slice of lemon peel.

name: Yellow Bird
recipe: Shake 3 shots of White Rum 1.5 shots of Galiano 1.5 shots of Triple Sec 1.5 shots of Lime juice and strain into a chilled cocktail glass

name: Zippy's Revenge
recipe: Mix Kool-Aid to taste then add 2 shots of Rum and 2 shots of Amaretto. Shake well to dissolve the sugar in the Kool-Aid... serve cold

name: Zorbatini
recipe: Pour 1.5 shots of vodka and 1/2 shot of Ouzo into a Martini glass. Garnish with a green olive.
